The paper discusses the development of bibliometric indicators for academic publishers based on books and book chapters. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybernetics (cs.CY), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on data processing and analysis, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
